<title>UK: Baltic Handy Index rose 13 points to 1,079.</title>
<headline>Baltic Handy Index rose 13 points to 1,079.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Baltic Handy Index for Handy size shipping rates rose to 1,079 on Thursday from 1,066 on Feb 20, with the base being Jan 7 1997 equals 1000. The BHI is based on the following routes with rates in dollars/tonne.</p>
<p> Route					 Weighting   Average   Prev</p>
<p>								   ($/Day)</p>
<p>1. Continent/Far East			 25 pct    12,667  12,600</p>
<p>2. Japan-S.Korea/NoPac or Australia RV  30	   9,250   8,958</p>
<p>3. Singapore/Australia/Continent	  15	   5,667   5,592</p>
<p>4. Continent/N or S.Atlantic RV	   30	   8,440   8,460</p>
<p>(All for 43,000 DWT)</p>
<p>Ongoing Trial Routes					     $/MT</p>
<p>T1 1.4-1.6 M 55' USG/Continent-Grains    -	    15.19  15.06</p>
<p>T2 28/32,000 53' Brazil/Continent-Grains -	    17.38  16.88</p>
<p>Note - The Index initially to be published each Tuesday and Thursday is derived from four Handymax time charter routes based on the 'Baltic Handy Max', a modern 43,000 DWT vessel with 25 ton cranes.  The Baltic Exchange will also publish returns on two other trial routes alongside the Index. They may be included in it at a later date.</p>
